Key Match Events: The Suns’ efficient offense and Utah’s cold 3-point shooting (9-of-42, 21.4 percent) proved to be too much to overcome, as Phoenix came away with a 114-106 victory.
Kyle Filipowski quickly racked up two steals and four points as Utah got within one point late in the first quarter.
Utah’s defense locked in to begin the second half, with an 11-0 scoring run eventually bringing Utah within just one point at 67-66.
Svi Mykhailiuk and Drew Eubanks combined for two pick-and-roll connections as Utah’s second unit continued to produce.
Former Jazzman Grayson Allen left his mark on the fourth quarter with three 3-pointers as the Suns once again pushed their lead to double digits.
Post-Match Reflections: Jazz head coach Will Hardy said, 'I thought the team played hard, but we just couldn’t get it going offensively. Some of that was that we just missed (shots). We’ll bounce back tomorrow, that’s the great thing about the NBA, the games just keep coming.'
Others: Williams impressed with a career-high 13 points off the bench, which included two confident 3-pointers from the wing.
Mykhailiuk was active early and often Saturday, finishing with 13 points and seven assists in his 19 minutes of action.
Eubanks set a new season-high with 11 rebounds in 17 minutes.
Two-Way guard Elijah Harkless made his NBA debut Saturday.
Booker led the way with 34 points in the win, while Durant contributed 25 points and seven assists.
As a team, the Suns connected on 51.2 percent from the field, which included 63.3 percent shooting inside the arc.
Collier racked up another eight assists against the Suns, using his speed and athleticism to create other opportunities for teammates both around the rim and beyond the arc.
